==Demographics==
As of the 2020 census, there were 347 people, 173 housing units, and 276 families in the CDP. The racial makeup was 96.5% [[White Americans|White]], 0.6% [[Asian Americans|Asian]], and 2.9% from [[Multiracial Americans|two or more races]]. A total of 0.6% of the population had [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] origin.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile?g=160XX00US2159592 |access-date=2023-06-20 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

The ancestry was 30.8% [[Americans|American]], 13.0% [[English Americans|English]], 9.5% [[Irish Americans|Irish]], 6.4% [[German Americans|German]], 2.3% [[French Americans|French]], and 2.3% [[Scottish Americans|Scottish]].<ref name=":0" />

The median age was 38.2 years old. A total of 5.6% of the population were 65 or older, with 3.1% between the ages of 65 and 74, and 2.4% between the ages of 75 and 84. A total of 29.0% of the population were under 18, with 17.9% between the ages of 5 and 14, and 11.1% between the ages of 15 and 17.<ref name=":0" />

The median household income was $29,375. 47.0% of the population were in poverty.<ref name=":0" />{{US Census population
